Definition: adhering to an attitude or position widely held to be outmoded
Example: peasants are still unreconstructed small capitalists at heart; there are probably more unreconstructed Southerners than one would like to admit
Synonyms: RECONSTRUCTED, adhering, to, an, attitude, or, position, widely, held, be, outmoded, peasants, are, still, unreconstructed, small, capitalists, at, heart, there, probably, more, Southerners, than, one, would, like, admit
Category: adj.all
